io.micronaut.context

Interface ExecutionHandleLocator

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ApplicationContext, BeanContext
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultApplicationContext, DefaultBeanContext

    public interface ExecutionHandleLocator
    Interface for components that are able to locate and return ExecutionHandle instances for beans.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Graeme Rocher

      • findExecutionHandle

        <R> Optional<MethodExecutionHandle<R>> findExecutionHandle(Class<?> beanType,
                                                           String method,
                                                           Class... arguments)
        Finds an optimized execution handle for invoking a bean method. The execution handle may or may not be implemented by generated byte code.
        Type Parameters:
        R - The result type of the execution handle
        Parameters:
        beanType - The bean type
        method - The method
        arguments - The arguments
        Returns:
        The execution handle
